<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="197" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,384,684]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">
<bibRefCitation author="Ghiliani, V." box="[151,313,384,407]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="195 - 381" refId="ref2538" refString="Ghiliani, V. (1887) Elenco delle specie di coleotteri trovate in Piemonte. Opera postuma pubblicata per cura del Membro ordinario Dott. Lorenzo Camerano. Annali della Reale Accademia d'Agricoltura di Torino, 29 (1886), 195 - 381." type="journal article" year="1887">Ghiliani (1887</bibRefCitation>
: 300) considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Ponza" authorityName="Ponza" authorityYear="1805" box="[508,705,384,407]" class="Insecta" family="Attelabidae" genus="Attelabus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funereus">
<emphasis box="[508,631,384,407]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">A. funereus</emphasis>
Ponza
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[904,1054,384,407]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Clerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mutillarius">
<emphasis box="[904,1054,384,407]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">C. mutillarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The synonymy was listed also by 
<bibRefCitation author="Luigioni, P." box="[151,317,418,441]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="1 - 1159" refId="ref3022" refString="Luigioni, P. (1929) I Coleotteri d'Italia. Catalogo sinonimico-topografico-bibliografico. Memorie della Pontificia Accademia delle Scienze, I Nuovi Lincei, Series 2, 13, (4) + 1 - 1159 + (1)." type="journal article" year="1929">Luigioni (1929</bibRefCitation>
: 636), as 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius" authorityName="Fabricius" box="[424,812,418,441]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pseudoclerops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mutillarius">
<emphasis box="[424,705,418,441]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Pseudoclerops mutillarius</emphasis>
Fabricius
</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName authority="Ponza" authorityName="Ponza" authorityYear="1805" box="[844,1012,418,441]" class="Insecta" family="Attelabidae" genus="Attelabus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funereus">
<emphasis box="[844,934,418,441]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">funereus</emphasis>
Ponza
</taxonomicName>
, but was mostly overlooked otherwise. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dutto, M. &amp; Poggi, R. &amp; Cavazzuti, P. F." box="[151,351,453,476]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="347 - 458" refId="ref2368" refString="Dutto, M., Poggi, R. &amp; Cavazzuti, P. F. (2009) I &quot; Coleoptera Salutiensia &quot; di Lorenzo Ponza (1805), con dati bio-bibliografici sull'autore e alcune note. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; G. Doria &quot;, 100, 347 - 458." type="journal article" year="2009">
Dutto 
<emphasis box="[220,269,453,476]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">et al</emphasis>
. (2009
</bibRefCitation>
: 428) quoted that two anonymous hand-written notes in French on a copy of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ponza, L." box="[1199,1362,453,476]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="29 - 94" refId="ref3148" refString="Ponza, L. (1805) Coleoptera salutiensia sive enumeratio methodica coleopterorum, quae in agro salutiensi reperiuntur, locorum natalium indicatione, observationibus, novisque aliquot speciebus aucta. Memoires de l'Academie Imperiale des Sciences, Litterature et Beaux-Arts de Turin. Sciences Physiques et Mathematiques, 12 - 13 (1804 / 5), 29 - 94, pls. IV-V." type="journal article" year="1805">Ponza’s (1805)</bibRefCitation>
paper, conserved in the library of the Museo Civico di Storia Naturale “G. Doria” (Genova), refer this name to 
<taxonomicName box="[1280,1429,488,511]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pseudoclerops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mutillarius">
<emphasis box="[1280,1429,488,511]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">C. mutillarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Original description and illustration confirm the synonymy with the nominal subspecies. No specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ponza" authorityYear="1805" box="[1314,1436,522,545]" class="Insecta" family="Attelabidae" genus="Attelabus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funereus">
<emphasis box="[1314,1436,522,545]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">A. funereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found in the rich Massimiliano Spinola collection (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ekis, G." box="[787,897,557,580]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref2426" refString="Ekis, G. (1975) Taxonomic and nomenclatural status of clerid taxa described by Massimiliano Spinola (1780 - 1857) (Coleoptera, Cleridae). Bollettino del Museo di Zoologia dell'Universita di Torino, 1, 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="1975">Ekis 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Giachino, P. M." box="[909,1070,557,580]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="1 - 616" refId="ref2584" refString="Giachino, P. M. (1982) Collezione coleotterologica di Massimiliano Spinola. Cataloghi-Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali, Torino, 3, 1 - 616." type="journal article" year="1982">Giachino 1982</bibRefCitation>
), in spite of Spinola—&quot;the superb cleridologist of his time&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Ekis, G." box="[430,542,592,615]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref2426" refString="Ekis, G. (1975) Taxonomic and nomenclatural status of clerid taxa described by Massimiliano Spinola (1780 - 1857) (Coleoptera, Cleridae). Bollettino del Museo di Zoologia dell'Universita di Torino, 1, 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="1975">Ekis 1975</bibRefCitation>
: 2)—was active in the same region where Ponza lived (Conci &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poggi, R. &amp; Conci, C." box="[1233,1358,592,615]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="3 - 157" refId="ref3114" refString="Poggi, R. &amp; Conci, C. (1996) Elenco delle collezioni entomologiche conservate nelle strutture pubbliche italiane. Memorie della Societa entomologica italiana, 75, 3 - 157." type="journal article" year="1996">Poggi 1996</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,384,684]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">
<taxonomicName authority="mutillarius" authorityName="mutillarius Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[199,522,626,649]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Clerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="mutillarius" subSpecies="mutillarius">
<emphasis box="[199,522,626,649]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Clerus mutillarius mutillarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread across all of 
<collectingCountry box="[832,881,626,649]" name="Italy" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Italy</collectingCountry>
(including 
<collectingRegion box="[1009,1071,626,649]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Sicily</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1128,1218,626,649]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Cornacchia, P." box="[1242,1428,626,649]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="822 - 831" refId="ref2239" refString="Cornacchia, P. (2011) Short notes 4. Coleoptera, Cleridae. In: Nardi, G., Whitmore, D., Bardiani, M., Birtele, D., Mason, F., Spada, L. &amp; Cerretti, P. (Eds.), Biodiversity of Marganai and Montimannu (Sardinia). Research in the framework of the ICP Forests network. Conservazione Habitat Invertebrati, 5, pp. 822 - 831." type="journal article" year="2011">Cornacchia 2011</bibRefCitation>
) but, from a conservation point of view, is classified as “Near Threatened” (
<bibRefCitation author="Audisio, P. &amp; Zappi, I. &amp; Liberto, A." box="[948,1158,661,684]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="75 - 76" refId="ref1892" refString="Audisio, P., Zappi, I. &amp; Liberto, A. (2015) Family Cleridae. In: Carpaneto, G. M., Baviera, C., Biscaccianti, A. B., Brandmayr, P., Mazzei, A., Mason, F., Battistoni, A., Teofli, C., Rondinini, C., Fattorini, S. &amp; Audisio, P. (Eds.), A Red List of Italian Saproxylic Beetles: taxonomic overview, ecological features and conservation issues (Coleoptera). Fragmenta entomologica, 47 (2), pp. 75 - 76." type="journal article" year="2015">
Audisio 
<emphasis box="[1041,1088,661,684]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
